exp: The image shows vitelline and umbilical veins development during liver development. question: The marked cell inhibits which of the following structure:
exp: The present slide shows the Purkinje cell in middle layer of cerebellar coex. They inhibit the deep cerebellar nuclei. Identification: Purkinje cells are the largest of five cell types in the cerebellar coex. Lie in the middle layer (cerebellar coex is three layered). Send dendritic process towards the outer molecular layer. Note: Outer molecular has less density of cells, as compared with inner granular layer with high density of cells. Details: Purkinje cells are a class of GABAergic neuro inhibitory neurons sending projections to the deep cerebellar nuclei (e. g., dentate nucleus). They are the only cells carrying output (efferent) fibres from cerebellar coex.

question: Teiary stem villi consists of:-
exp: Secondary villi:- contains a central core of primary (extra embryonic) mesoderm and is covered by cyto- and syncytio- trophoblast cells. Teiary villicontains fetal blood vessels invading the extra embryonic mesoderm and is covered by trophoblastic cells.
opa: Central core of cytotrophoblast covered with synctiotrophoblast
opb: Central core of extra-embryonic mesoderm covered by central cyto- and peripheral synctio- trophoblast
opc: Central maternal blood vessels surrounded by mesoderm and trophoblast
opd: Central fetal blood vessels surrounded by mesoderm and trophoblast

question: A paial development of the aoicopulmonary septum will result in which of the following?
exp: A. Paial development of the aoicopulmonary septum due to absence of migration of neural crest cell to truncus aeriosus region will cause persistent truncus aeriosus(PTA). FIG:- PTA
